cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning models for automatic plaque detection in intravascular optical coherence tomography (IVOCT) images. This involves image classification and feature extraction, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning models also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and clinical decision support systems, which are relevant to the sub-categories of medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
